Figma Reference

https://www.figma.com/design/8D5SBb4qOkelVBDEANzwc2/DPWorld-Design-System?node-id=6867-15009&m=dev 

Description:

Component is global and can be viewed on all site pages

Component to include 3 main sections:

Logo

Quick Links

Social Icons and Bottom links

Functional requirements/ Acceptance criteria:

As an end user, 

I can click on the Logo to land on the DPW Homepage

I can find a main column title within Quick links section - not clickable

I can find a main column title within Quick Links section - clickable (only when a link is added for it in CMS)

I can click on the link titles under the the main column title within Quick links section

I can find generic page links at the bottom clickable to open to respective site pages (alignment to follow as per design)

I can find social links redirecting users to business pages on respective social channels  (alignment to follow as per design)

I can see translated content for region specific sites

I can hover over the links to find a hover effect as per the website style guidelines 

I can find contact information with a phone number (respective to region sites) where the phone number is clickable to open with a call application from web or mobile [Client wanted to redirect this to a webform instead of direct click but decision on implementation can be made with new IA] [Discussed with Sneha]

Decision: Add a link field for managing this. If not provided, link the telephone number as default behaviour.

As a content author,

I can update the logo and the link on the logo

I can add/ update/delete quick links with main title (max 140 char), link title (max 130 char) and linked url on the title

I can add/update/delete the link text and link urls for the bottom links

I can add/update/delete the social icons and their links from CMS

Design Notes:

Footer to scale in full width for all site pages

Alignment of elements to follow as per design for Desktop specific to languages

Mobile Designs

Elements to stack as per design reference

Field Level Requirements:

Component Distribution

Element

Name of element on the rendering (ex: Headline, CTA Link)

Field Type

(ex: multi-line text, drop down menu, image)

Field Note

required or optional in CMS

Data Source

Content Managed or integrated into another system?

Display

Field-level display rules (ex: left aligned, max char count, user interactions) . Identify if the display is internal (content author) or external (site visitor).

Notes

Footer

Logo

Browse Media

Optional

Content managed

aligned as per design reference

In CMS, authors can revise the logo image



Logo Link

Link field

Optional

Content Managed



In CMS, authors can add a link that can be navigated when the user clicks on the logo in the footer



Quick Links

Tree List/ Multi-list

Required

Content Managed

Aligned as per design reference

Authors can include Max 6 Quick link section Item titles to display in column distribution as per design

Authors can sort these titles to show in order as required



Bottom links

Tree list/ multi-list

Required

Content Managed

Aligned as per design reference

authors can add max 5 links to display in single row

if more added, a items should fall in new row(Tech confirmed with Design: If there are more than 5 links then it will cover the remaining space before the social icons section and then move to the second row. The placement of social icons will remain the same.)

Quick Links Section Items

Item Main title

Single line text

Required

Content Managed

Aligned in columns as per design

Stacked above all sub links





Item Main title link

Link field

Optional

Content Managed



authors can add links that can be clicked from the main column title



Item sub title

Single line text

Required

Content Managed

Aligned in columns per design

Stacked below main column title





Item sub title link url

Link field

Optional

Content Managed



authors can add links that can be clicked from the main column title

Title to display as basic text when not linked with url

As discussed on 7 April - the link is required for displaying 



Item Phone number

Number + Character field

Optional

Content Managed

Aligned in columns per design

Stacked below main column title or sub text if any

authors can add number that can be used for calling with single click

Bottom Link Items

Title

Single line field

Required

Content Managed

Aligned in columns on single row as per design

authors can add/ update/ remove the titles 



Title Link

Link field

Optional

Content Managed



authors can add links that can be clicked from the titles

Social Media Items

Social Media icon

Browse media

Required

Content Managed

Aligned as per design reference in single row

authors can add/ update/ remove icons 

Max 5-6 icons recommended

SVG icons should be used



Social Media links

Link field

Required

Content Managed



authors can add links that can be clicked from icons for user to navigate to social media pages to social media pages

